Comparison: Shared vs. Local
| Feature | ReentrantLock (Shared) | ThreadLocal (Private) |
|---|---|---|
| Strategy | Synchronization (Wait your turn) | Isolation (Everyone gets their own) |
| Performance | Slower (Wait/Context Switch) | Fast (No contention) |
| Memory | Low (One variable) | Higher (Variable per thread) |
| Best For | Databases, Shared Counters | User Sessions, DB Connections, Transaction IDs |
